I did not like this course very much. In my opinion, this one should not be a part of the specialization. The course is not very useful. Perhaps, I simply did not need this course, but it was a must to accomplish a specialization. Anyway, thank you and sorry for not being satisfied with this one.
not getting peer reviews thats why I can't able to get the certificate.
generally good

All is good (e.g., the lectures, quizzes, assignments) except that the points on Peer-Graded Assignment (PGA) has weight on the final grade. I get 100% on my quizzes on first take but got low grade on one of the week because of low points on PGA. I had to resubmit my assignment and wait for another days for it to be reviewed. It's sad when a peer reviewed your work with low points w/o basing on the criteria. The PGA is helpful, but based on the 10+ PGA's I'd reviewed in every week, MOST don't follow what is taught on the lecture and still do the usual format in internet. Some even passed blank assignment. Most took this course only for certificates but it is important also that they learn what is being taught.
Not very interesting lessons. English gamma too simple. Very little additional material. Two other courses are made much better.
There's one of my assigments which hasn't been checked yet. It's been more than three weeks since I sent it.
The instructor has put all efforts to teach, write a professional e-portfolio. Good job. However, the peer-reviewed assignment for providing links would be difficult to most of the students.

In my country and field is not very common that you present an e-portafolio for seeking a job. In some way the course helped to write my resume in english. But I thing, the lessons could be more interactive and also have more examples in other fields, for instance law and social science.
entry-level
My peer review of week 3 is still waiting to be reviewed, meanwhile, I was still paying for the course and because of that, I couldn't enroll in the next course.

The View on Mobile app and Desktop is so different.  When I posted week two work an old website I'd built populated.  I didn't have time to even notice it.  It did not meet assignment rubric.  And once my classmates reviewed it and moved on I was forced to switch sessions because "nobody" was left to grade any resubmissions.  That should have been visible in the mobile app.  For a week I kept searching for the "problem" and the mobile app said all complete, the desktop assignment tab finally revealed my issue.
